# RapidAid Live Tracking UI Design

## Purpose

The Live Tracking Page allows patients, ambulance drivers, hospitals, and emergency contacts to monitor the ambulance's real-time location, estimated arrival time (ETA), and route information.

## Page Layout

### Header

- 🚑 RapidAid Logo
- Dashboard
- Emergency Status
- Notifications
- Profile

## Live Map Section

Display:

- Patient Location
- Ambulance Live Location
- Assigned Hospital
- Best Route
- Traffic Conditions

Map Controls:

- Zoom In
- Zoom Out
- Current Location
- Full Screen

---

## Ambulance Information

Display:

- Ambulance Number
- Driver Name
- Driver Contact
- Vehicle Type
- Current Speed
- Current Status

Status Examples:

- Request Accepted
- En Route
- Near Patient
- Patient On Board
- Reached Hospital

---

## Estimated Arrival Time (ETA)

Display:

- Distance to Patient
- Estimated Arrival Time
- Estimated Hospital Arrival
- Traffic Delay

---

## Route Information

Show:

- Total Distance
- Remaining Distance
- Fastest Route
- Alternate Route (if available)

---

## Hospital Details

Display:

- Hospital Name
- Address
- Emergency Department
- Available ICU Beds
- Available Doctors

Button:

- View Hospital Details

---

## Emergency Contact Updates

Automatically share:

- Live Location
- Ambulance Status
- ETA
- Assigned Hospital

---

## Live Notifications

Examples:

- Ambulance Accepted Your Request
- Ambulance is 5 Minutes Away
- Patient Picked Up
- Arrived at Hospital
- Treatment Started

---

